{"video_id": "YrmgHs-Vaik", "title": "Daily Evening Bhagavatam Discourse | HH Stoka Krishna Swami | SB 1.15.49 | 04-01-2023", "speaker": "HH Stoka Krishna Swami", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YrmgHs-Vaik", "duration": 896, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 9.68, "text": " Om Agyana Timiraandhasya Gyananjanishalakaya Chaksharunmilitam Yena Tasmai Shri Gurave Namaha"}, {"start": 9.68, "end": 17.8, "text": " Nama Om Vishnupadaya Krishna Preshtaya Bhutale Shri Mate Bhaktivedanta Swamin Nithinamine"}, {"start": 17.8, "end": 26.46, "text": " Namaste Saraswate Deve Gauravani Pracharine Nirvishesha Shunyavadi Pashchatyade Shatarine"}, {"start": 26.46, "end": 35.36, "text": " Jaya Shri Krishna Chaitanya Prabhu Nithyananda Shri Advaita Gadadhara Srivasa Adi Gauravakta Vrinda"}, {"start": 35.36, "end": 43.74, "text": " Hare Krishna Hare Krishna Krishna Krishna Hare Hare Hare Rama Hare Rama Rama Rama Hare Hare"}, {"start": 43.74, "end": 50.68, "text": " Om Namo Bhagavate Vasudevaya Narayanam Namaskritya Naram Chai Vanarottamam"}, {"start": 50.68, "end": 55.58, "text": " Devi Saraswati Vyasam Tato Jayam Udi Rayet"}, {"start": 56.46, "end": 65.24, "text": " In this session we will be discussing from the 49th verse of the 15th chapter of the 1st canto of Srimad Bhagavatam."}, {"start": 65.24, "end": 80.64, "text": " Vidropi Parityajya Prabhase Deham Atmanaha Krishna Aveshenata Chittaha Pitrabhir Svakshayam Yayau"}, {"start": 86.46000000000001, "end": 93.16000000000001, "text": " The meaning of this verse is, Vidura, while on pilgrimage, left his body at Prabhasa."}, {"start": 93.92, "end": 101.24000000000001, "text": " Because he was absorbed in thought of Lord Krishna, he was received by the denizens of Pitraloka planet,"}, {"start": 101.84, "end": 104.4, "text": " where he returned to his original post."}, {"start": 108.4, "end": 115.20000000000002, "text": " So now, after having described the Pandavas,"}, {"start": 116.46000000000001, "end": 120.00000000000001, "text": " they returned to Krishna's personal abode."}, {"start": 121.74000000000001, "end": 124.36000000000001, "text": " Now the description is being given of Vidura."}, {"start": 125.64000000000001, "end": 130.8, "text": " Earlier we had heard how Vidura instructed Dhritarashtra"}, {"start": 130.8, "end": 139.14000000000001, "text": " to prepare himself for quitting the body and attaining self-realization."}, {"start": 139.14000000000001, "end": 146.14000000000001, "text": " So now Vidura himself, he was constantly absorbed in thought of Krishna."}, {"start": 146.46, "end": 154.46, "text": " Therefore, when he left his body, he went back to his original post in Pitraloka."}, {"start": 155.24, "end": 158.10000000000002, "text": " So Srila Prabhupada explains this point in the purport."}, {"start": 159.38, "end": 162.74, "text": " The difference between the Pandavas and Vidura is that"}, {"start": 162.74, "end": 168.0, "text": " the Pandavas are eternal associates of the Lord, the Personality of Godhead."}, {"start": 168.70000000000002, "end": 175.94, "text": " Whereas Vidura is one of the administrative demigods in charge of the Pitraloka planet,"}, {"start": 176.46, "end": 179.46, "text": " and is known as Yama-Raj."}, {"start": 179.46, "end": 184.46, "text": " Vidura is an incarnation of Yama-Raj."}, {"start": 184.46, "end": 190.46, "text": " Yama-Raj is always a pure devotee of the Supreme Lord."}, {"start": 190.46, "end": 201.46, "text": " Even in his Pitraloka planet, he is always in the position of being a pure devotee of the Supreme Lord."}, {"start": 201.46, "end": 205.46, "text": " So his devotion and service is eternal."}, {"start": 206.46, "end": 219.46, "text": " He also has got a responsibility of punishing the sinful people, extremely sinful people in the post of Yama-Raj."}, {"start": 219.46, "end": 231.46, "text": " So he is not like the other devatas who have got a desire for material enjoyment and therefore they occupy a post."}, {"start": 231.46, "end": 232.46, "text": " No."}, {"start": 232.46, "end": 234.46, "text": " Yama-Raj is not like that."}, {"start": 234.46, "end": 235.46, "text": " Vidura is not like that."}, {"start": 235.46, "end": 243.46, "text": " So Srila Prabhupada says about Vidura as Yama-Raj,"}, {"start": 243.46, "end": 250.46, "text": " Men are afraid of Yama-Raj because it is he only who awards punishment to the miscreants of the material world."}, {"start": 250.46, "end": 261.46000000000004, "text": " Those who are very very sinful, they are punished by Yama-Raj by being sent to hellish planets for punishment."}, {"start": 261.46000000000004, "end": 264.46000000000004, "text": " Hellish planets are not places of inhabitation for any kind."}, {"start": 264.46, "end": 266.46, "text": " They are not places of inhabitation for any condition."}, {"start": 266.46, "end": 272.46, "text": " So it is exclusively meant for giving punishment to extremely sinful persons."}, {"start": 272.46, "end": 280.46, "text": " So these miscreants, sinful people, they are afraid of Yama-Raj."}, {"start": 280.46, "end": 288.46, "text": " But those who are devotees of the Lord have nothing to fear from him because he himself is a devotee."}, {"start": 288.46, "end": 292.46, "text": " Yama-Raj is devotee, pure devotee."}, {"start": 292.46, "end": 298.46, "text": " So other devotees, pure devotees of the Lord have nothing to fear from Yama-Raj."}, {"start": 298.46, "end": 306.46, "text": " To the devotees, Yama-Raj is a cordial friend."}, {"start": 306.46, "end": 310.46, "text": " But to the non-devotees, he is fear personified."}, {"start": 310.46, "end": 320.46, "text": " He is doing his duty of punishing the non-devotees who are engaged in grievous sinful activities."}, {"start": 322.46, "end": 336.46, "text": " As we have already discussed, it is understood that Yama-Raj was cursed by Manduka Muni to be degraded as a Shudra."}, {"start": 336.46, "end": 350.46, "text": " Once Yama-Raj made a mistake in the past that this Manduka Muni who did some mistake when he was a small boy,"}, {"start": 350.46, "end": 356.46, "text": " he was punished later on for the mistake innocently committed."}, {"start": 356.46, "end": 366.46, "text": " So Manduka Muni became angry and he cursed Yama-Raj to take birth as the son of a Shudrani,"}, {"start": 366.46, "end": 370.46, "text": " a maidservant, Dasiputra."}, {"start": 370.46, "end": 376.46, "text": " So that curse, because the curse, even though he is a pure devotee,"}, {"start": 376.46, "end": 380.46, "text": " he accepted the curse and therefore he had to take birth as Vidura."}, {"start": 380.46, "end": 386.46, "text": " But as the son of a maidservant."}, {"start": 386.46, "end": 398.46, "text": " So he was, Yama-Raj was born as Vidura, considered as a Shudra."}, {"start": 398.46, "end": 404.46, "text": " Therefore Vidura was an incarnation of Yama-Raj."}, {"start": 404.46, "end": 410.46, "text": " Because he is cursed to take birth as a Shudra."}, {"start": 410.46000000000004, "end": 418.46000000000004, "text": " As an eternal servitor of the Lord, he displayed his devotional activities very ardently"}, {"start": 418.46000000000004, "end": 422.46000000000004, "text": " and lived a life of a pious man."}, {"start": 422.46000000000004, "end": 426.46000000000004, "text": " Devotees always live a pious life."}, {"start": 426.46000000000004, "end": 430.46000000000004, "text": " They don't commit sinful activities."}, {"start": 430.46000000000004, "end": 434.46000000000004, "text": " This is the wonderful nature or characteristic of a devotee."}, {"start": 434.46000000000004, "end": 436.46000000000004, "text": " Even in this material world."}, {"start": 436.46000000000004, "end": 438.46000000000004, "text": " Even if they are harassed."}, {"start": 438.46000000000004, "end": 440.46000000000004, "text": " Even if they are insulted."}, {"start": 440.46000000000004, "end": 442.46000000000004, "text": " Even if they are cheated."}, {"start": 442.46000000000004, "end": 450.46000000000004, "text": " Even if the others try to mislead them."}, {"start": 450.46000000000004, "end": 454.46000000000004, "text": " They are fixed in devotional service."}, {"start": 454.46000000000004, "end": 456.46000000000004, "text": " They don't get misled."}, {"start": 456.46000000000004, "end": 460.46000000000004, "text": " On the other hand, it is described here,"}, {"start": 460.46000000000004, "end": 464.46000000000004, "text": " such pure devotees as Vidura,"}, {"start": 464.46000000000004, "end": 468.46000000000004, "text": " about them Prabhupada is telling,"}, {"start": 468.46000000000004, "end": 476.46000000000004, "text": " that Vidura lived a life of a pious man"}, {"start": 476.46000000000004, "end": 478.46000000000004, "text": " so much so that"}, {"start": 478.46000000000004, "end": 480.46000000000004, "text": " a materialistic man like Dhritarashtra"}, {"start": 480.46000000000004, "end": 484.46000000000004, "text": " also got salvation by his instruction."}, {"start": 484.46000000000004, "end": 488.46000000000004, "text": " Dhritarashtra was very materialistic."}, {"start": 488.46000000000004, "end": 492.46000000000004, "text": " But even Dhritarashtra got salvation or moksha"}, {"start": 492.46000000000004, "end": 496.46000000000004, "text": " by the instructions of Vidura."}, {"start": 496.46000000000004, "end": 502.46000000000004, "text": " What is the connection between Vidura and Dhritarashtra?"}, {"start": 502.46000000000004, "end": 516.46, "text": " Both are born as sons of Vichitravirya."}, {"start": 516.46, "end": 524.46, "text": " But Vidura was born as a son of a maid servant"}, {"start": 524.46, "end": 526.46, "text": " of one of the queens of Vichitravirya."}, {"start": 526.46, "end": 532.46, "text": " And Dhritarashtra was born as the son of the queen"}, {"start": 532.46, "end": 534.46, "text": " of Vichitravirya."}, {"start": 534.46, "end": 538.46, "text": " So Dhritarashtra had a share in"}, {"start": 538.46, "end": 542.46, "text": " the inheritance of the kingdom."}, {"start": 542.46, "end": 544.46, "text": " But Vidura had no share."}, {"start": 544.46, "end": 548.46, "text": " So Vidura accepted his position as the"}, {"start": 554.46, "end": 556.46, "text": " Shudra."}, {"start": 556.46, "end": 562.46, "text": " But Dhritarashtra as a Kshatriya,"}, {"start": 562.46, "end": 566.46, "text": " he became the caretaker king of the entire world."}, {"start": 566.46, "end": 570.46, "text": " So Dhritarashtra was very materialistic,"}, {"start": 570.46, "end": 574.46, "text": " but by the instruction of Vidura,"}, {"start": 574.46, "end": 578.46, "text": " he was able to get moksha,"}, {"start": 578.46, "end": 580.46, "text": " salvation."}, {"start": 580.46, "end": 582.46, "text": " So therefore Prabhupada says,"}, {"start": 582.46, "end": 584.46, "text": " Vidura by his pious activities"}, {"start": 584.46, "end": 586.46, "text": " in the devotional service"}, {"start": 586.46, "end": 588.46, "text": " of the Lord,"}, {"start": 588.46, "end": 590.46, "text": " was able to always remember"}, {"start": 590.46, "end": 592.46, "text": " the lotus feet of the Lord."}, {"start": 596.46, "end": 598.46, "text": " So remembering constantly"}, {"start": 598.46, "end": 600.46, "text": " the lotus feet of the Lord"}, {"start": 600.46, "end": 602.46, "text": " is a devotional service."}, {"start": 606.46, "end": 608.46, "text": " And that is possible"}, {"start": 608.46, "end": 610.46, "text": " by constant engagement"}, {"start": 610.46, "end": 614.46, "text": " in devotional activities."}, {"start": 616.46, "end": 618.46, "text": " This remembrance is not"}, {"start": 618.46, "end": 620.46, "text": " some idle meditation"}, {"start": 620.46, "end": 622.46, "text": " or lazily sitting"}, {"start": 622.46, "end": 624.46, "text": " in the excuse of doing meditation"}, {"start": 624.46, "end": 626.46, "text": " and actually sleeping."}, {"start": 626.46, "end": 628.46, "text": " No, it's not that."}, {"start": 632.46, "end": 634.46, "text": " Now by constantly remembering"}, {"start": 634.46, "end": 636.46, "text": " the lotus feet of the Lord,"}, {"start": 636.46, "end": 638.46, "text": " Vidura became washed of all"}, {"start": 638.46, "end": 640.46, "text": " contamination of a Shudra-born life."}, {"start": 642.46, "end": 644.46, "text": " Actually as a pure devotee"}, {"start": 644.46, "end": 646.46, "text": " there is no contamination, but even"}, {"start": 646.46, "end": 648.46, "text": " if there were any contamination"}, {"start": 648.46, "end": 650.46, "text": " due to taking birth"}, {"start": 650.46, "end": 652.46, "text": " as a Shudra and engaging"}, {"start": 652.46, "end": 654.46, "text": " in such Shudra activities,"}, {"start": 654.46, "end": 656.46, "text": " still he became free"}, {"start": 656.46, "end": 658.46, "text": " from all contamination"}, {"start": 658.46, "end": 660.46, "text": " by his constant remembrance"}, {"start": 660.46, "end": 662.46, "text": " of the lotus feet"}, {"start": 662.46, "end": 664.46, "text": " of the Supreme Lord."}, {"start": 668.46, "end": 670.46, "text": " In many places in scripture it is said"}, {"start": 670.46, "end": 672.46, "text": " one who constantly thinks of Krishna"}, {"start": 672.46, "end": 674.46, "text": " becomes fully purified."}, {"start": 676.46, "end": 678.46, "text": " At the end"}, {"start": 680.46, "end": 682.46, "text": " he was received"}, {"start": 682.46, "end": 684.46, "text": " again by the denizens"}, {"start": 684.46, "end": 686.46, "text": " of Pitraloka"}, {"start": 686.46, "end": 688.46, "text": " and posted in his original"}, {"start": 688.46, "end": 690.46, "text": " position."}, {"start": 690.46, "end": 692.46, "text": " He came from Pitraloka"}, {"start": 692.46, "end": 694.46, "text": " he went back to Pitraloka."}, {"start": 698.46, "end": 700.46, "text": " So Srila Prabhupada says"}, {"start": 700.46, "end": 702.46, "text": " the demigods are also associates"}, {"start": 702.46, "end": 704.46, "text": " of the Lord without personal touch"}, {"start": 704.46, "end": 706.46, "text": " whereas the direct associates"}, {"start": 706.46, "end": 708.46, "text": " of the Lord are in constant"}, {"start": 708.46, "end": 710.46, "text": " personal touch with him."}, {"start": 710.46, "end": 712.46, "text": " What is the difference between"}, {"start": 712.46, "end": 714.46, "text": " Pandavas and Vidura?"}, {"start": 714.46, "end": 716.46, "text": " Pandavas are in constant touch"}, {"start": 716.46, "end": 718.46, "text": " with the Supreme Lord"}, {"start": 718.46, "end": 720.46, "text": " as his direct associates."}, {"start": 728.46, "end": 730.46, "text": " The"}, {"start": 730.46, "end": 732.46, "text": " demigods"}, {"start": 732.46, "end": 734.46, "text": " like Yamaraj"}, {"start": 734.46, "end": 736.46, "text": " they are also"}, {"start": 736.46, "end": 738.46, "text": " associates of the Lord"}, {"start": 738.46, "end": 740.46, "text": " but they don't have that personal touch."}, {"start": 740.46, "end": 742.46, "text": " They participate in the Lord's"}, {"start": 742.46, "end": 744.46, "text": " pastimes"}, {"start": 744.46, "end": 746.46, "text": " when they are"}, {"start": 746.46, "end": 748.46, "text": " given an opportunity"}, {"start": 748.46, "end": 750.46, "text": " because"}, {"start": 750.46, "end": 752.46, "text": " Lord's pastimes are"}, {"start": 752.46, "end": 754.46, "text": " an internal potency."}, {"start": 754.46, "end": 756.46, "text": " So"}, {"start": 756.46, "end": 758.46, "text": " unless they are"}, {"start": 758.46, "end": 760.46, "text": " given an opportunity"}, {"start": 760.46, "end": 762.46, "text": " they have to"}, {"start": 762.46, "end": 764.46, "text": " engage"}, {"start": 764.46, "end": 766.46, "text": " in such devotional activities as"}, {"start": 766.46, "end": 768.46, "text": " constantly remembering the Lord"}, {"start": 768.46, "end": 770.46, "text": " constantly hearing"}, {"start": 770.46, "end": 772.46, "text": " the glories of the Lord"}, {"start": 772.46, "end": 774.46, "text": " from the Bhagavatam"}, {"start": 774.46, "end": 776.46, "text": " constantly chanting and hearing the Holy Name"}, {"start": 776.46, "end": 778.46, "text": " there is"}, {"start": 778.46, "end": 780.46, "text": " constant association"}, {"start": 780.46, "end": 782.46, "text": " constant engagement"}, {"start": 782.46, "end": 784.46, "text": " in devotional service."}, {"start": 786.46, "end": 788.46, "text": " So Srila Prabhupada says"}, {"start": 788.46, "end": 790.46, "text": " further the Lord and his"}, {"start": 790.46, "end": 792.46, "text": " personal associates incarnate"}, {"start": 792.46, "end": 794.46, "text": " in many universes without"}, {"start": 794.46, "end": 796.46, "text": " cessation. Without cessation"}, {"start": 796.46, "end": 798.46, "text": " no stopping. No stoppage."}, {"start": 798.46, "end": 800.46, "text": " They continuously incarnate"}, {"start": 800.46, "end": 802.46, "text": " in many many universes."}, {"start": 802.46, "end": 804.46, "text": " Now"}, {"start": 804.46, "end": 806.46, "text": " the difference is"}, {"start": 806.46, "end": 808.46, "text": " between the Lord and his associates is"}, {"start": 808.46, "end": 810.46, "text": " the Lord remembers"}, {"start": 810.46, "end": 812.46, "text": " all of his previous"}, {"start": 812.46, "end": 814.46, "text": " incarnations"}, {"start": 814.46, "end": 816.46, "text": " whereas"}, {"start": 816.46, "end": 818.46, "text": " the associates forget due to their"}, {"start": 818.46, "end": 820.46, "text": " being very minute parts and parcels"}, {"start": 820.46, "end": 822.46, "text": " of the Lord."}, {"start": 822.46, "end": 824.46, "text": " We are very very"}, {"start": 824.46, "end": 826.46, "text": " tiny"}, {"start": 826.46, "end": 828.46, "text": " parts and parcels"}, {"start": 828.46, "end": 830.46, "text": " of the Lord."}, {"start": 830.46, "end": 832.46, "text": " Just like Arjuna"}, {"start": 832.46, "end": 834.46, "text": " Krishna tells Arjuna"}, {"start": 834.46, "end": 836.46, "text": " many many births"}, {"start": 836.46, "end": 838.46, "text": " you and I have taken"}, {"start": 838.46, "end": 840.46, "text": " in the past."}, {"start": 840.46, "end": 842.46, "text": " You and I have taken"}, {"start": 842.46, "end": 844.46, "text": " many many births"}, {"start": 844.46, "end": 846.46, "text": " in the past."}, {"start": 846.46, "end": 848.46, "text": " Now"}, {"start": 848.46, "end": 850.46, "text": " the Lord remembers"}, {"start": 850.46, "end": 852.46, "text": " all his previous"}, {"start": 852.46, "end": 854.46, "text": " incarnations."}, {"start": 854.46, "end": 856.46, "text": " I remember all of them"}, {"start": 856.46, "end": 858.46, "text": " but you"}, {"start": 858.46, "end": 860.46, "text": " do not."}, {"start": 860.46, "end": 862.46, "text": " So Prabhupada explains"}, {"start": 862.46, "end": 864.46, "text": " Arjuna is a pure devotee."}, {"start": 864.46, "end": 866.46, "text": " Arjuna is a constant companion"}, {"start": 866.46, "end": 868.46, "text": " of the Lord."}, {"start": 868.46, "end": 870.46, "text": " But he cannot remember his past"}, {"start": 870.46, "end": 872.46, "text": " appearances"}, {"start": 872.46, "end": 874.46, "text": " with the Lord."}, {"start": 874.46, "end": 876.46, "text": " He can't remember."}, {"start": 876.46, "end": 878.46, "text": " That Lord only knows."}, {"start": 878.46, "end": 880.46, "text": " Lord only can remember."}, {"start": 880.46, "end": 882.46, "text": " Because the Lord is supreme Lord"}, {"start": 882.46, "end": 884.46, "text": " unlimited Lord."}, {"start": 884.46, "end": 886.46, "text": " He has unlimited memory."}, {"start": 886.46, "end": 888.46, "text": " We are very very tiny part"}, {"start": 888.46, "end": 890.46, "text": " so we have limited memory."}, {"start": 890.46, "end": 892.46, "text": " Therefore this difference always exists."}, {"start": 892.46, "end": 894.46, "text": " I will stop here."}, {"start": 894.46, "end": 896.46, "text": " Thank you very much. Hare Krishna."}]}